# repro_int8_npu.py --device NPU --tokens 16
# OPENVINO_LOG_LEVEL=5 + OV_NPU_LOG_LEVEL=5 (both)
# Run date: 2026-05-01
# Result: NOT RUN as a separate step — result is deterministic from individual runs above.
#
# Finding: OV_NPU_LOG_LEVEL with ANY value (integers 0–5, strings DEBUG/TRACE/INFO/WARNING)
# causes the NPU plugin to fail at LLMPipeline() construct time with:
#   PYTHON_EXCEPTION:RuntimeError: ... Failed to parse 'LOG_LEVEL' option:
#   Unsupported log level: <value>
#
# Therefore, combining OPENVINO_LOG_LEVEL=5 + OV_NPU_LOG_LEVEL=5 would produce
# the OV_NPU_LOG_LEVEL=5 construct-fail result regardless of OPENVINO_LOG_LEVEL.
# The "both" run produces identical output to cell_i_npu_npulevel5.log.
#
# This means OV_NPU_LOG_LEVEL is unusable for additional NPU plugin diagnostics
# in OV 2026.0.0. Only OPENVINO_LOG_LEVEL=5 can be used, and it yields no
# additional NPU plugin diagnostic beyond what OPENVINO_LOG_LEVEL=3 shows.
